               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18411025-name-797" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18411025-name-797" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18411025-name-797" type="surname" value="SILVESTER"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18411025-name-797" type="given" value="GEORGE"></interp>GEORGE SILVESTER</persName>
                  </hi>. I am a shoemaker, and live in Ernest-street, Regent's-park. In August last, the prisoner came to ask me if a pair of shoes I was making for her was done—I said no, she should have them in a few days—after she was gone, I missed a pair of boots from the coun<lb></lb>ter—I did not suspect her, but when she was apprehended, a duplicate was brought to me—I went to the pawnbroker's and found my boots there.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Prisoner.</hi> At the time I went to his shop there was another girl with me <hi rend="italic">Witness.</hi> Yes, there was.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18411025-name-798" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18411025-name-798" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18411025-name-798" type="surname" value="BRADLEY"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18411025-name-798" type="given" value="RICHARD"></interp>RICHARD BRADLEY</persName>
                  </hi>. I am shopman to Livermore and Co., of Totten<lb></lb>ham-court-road. I produce a pair of women's boots, pawned on the 17th of August, by the prisoner, in the name of Ann Coleman—the duplicate produced is the one I gave for it—I knew her before, and am positive of her.</p>
