                        <interp inst="t18411025-name-799" type="given" value="JAMES"></interp>JAMES HILSDEN</persName>
                  </hi> (<hi rend="italic">police-constable S</hi> 42.) On the 22nd of October, I saw the prisoner in Cumberland-market—I asked her if her name was Coleman—she said, "No"—I asked if she knew anything of obtaining a basket of linen from Granby-street, the day before—she said, "No," she was not out all day, that she lived at No. 6, Fitzroy-row—I found her mother there, and found this duplicate amongst twenty-three in the room.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
